English subs for International Friends by yours Truly:
Y: Is there anything about you I need to know? Is everything okay?
J: Ah.
Y: Anything you really want me to know about you.
J: 0:08 For me, coffee.
Y: Coffee? You need to drink it?
J: I drink 7 cups a day.
Y: 7 glasses? Americano?
J: 0:19 Americano with a shot of Hazelnut coffee. (Mind you these descriptions are all in English, so for the average older Korean, it is as if in America some star says "I take my Champagne froid avec une peux de glace")
0:25 "subtitles says Jimmy is dizzy"
0:29 Y: Jessi, I'm not taking orders here.
0:33 J: It's an Americano, but you need a resonable amount of sugar.
0:28 Y: But it's not just any syrup. It needs to be hazelnut syrup. (Mind you most cafes in Korea don't have hazelnut syrup and there isn't a starbucks in every corner)
0:56 "subtitles says the deal is about to fall through even before any contract is signed"
0:57 J: For me it's either a Vanilla Latte or that. That's it. You can dress me in anything at all. 
1:02 Y: You're straight up lying.
1:06 J: Stylist, please come here. You can dress me in anything. 
1:09 Y: You mean it? Takes notes for himself: Can dress her in anything. I'm really going to believe you then.
1:12 J: I mean, it can't just be anything. 
1:17 Y: You just said we can dress you in anything at all. 
1:19 J: But that doesn't mean you can dress me in some huge dress with ruffles. I wouldn't wear something like that.
1:24 Y: Are you capricious?
1:25 J: Yes
1:27 Y: Takes notes for himself, "very capricious"
1:32 Y: Okay, then who do you think will be good as a manager?
1:33 J: Someone who is quickwitted. (In Korean sense means something who is quick and insightful to know what is precisely needed in a situation)
1:35 Y: What do you think of me? Am I quickwitted?
1:38 J: Of course, you are incredible. This guys isn't just any MC. He's the nation's MC. He's the best.
1:45 subtitle says "Just as satisfied as if she was complimenting himself (since he is Jimmy and not Yoo Jaesuk)"
1:50 J: That's how you got so far. You're the best.
1:52 Y: Someone recommended Gwanghee.
2:00 Y: Why?
2:01 J: Cause he's so nice. And his wit is the max.
2:05 Y: Oh really? Ah, Gwanghee. J: He is very quickwitted. No joke. 
2:07 Y: There was also talk of Saehyeong. And someone who mentioned Saeho.
2:11 J: Why is everyone Saewoo? (Saewoo in Korean means shrimp) Y: Not Saewoo. J: Saehyeong and Saewoo? Y: Saeho. J: Saeho and Saehyeong?
2:20 Y: You met him just a few days ago. J: Where? Y: When you appeared on Telegeuna. J: I appeared on Telegeuna? Y: Yes.
2:30 J: Saechan's little brother? Y: Saechan's older brother. J: Oh, he's older? Oh. NO.
2:45 J: Just Gwang. Let's go with Gwanghee. Y: What do you think of Saeho? J: Who is that? I'm sorry. Let me see a pic.
